pr_info.body:
This PR makes sure the signal `instr_multicycle_done_q` is only evaluated when the decoder currently has a multicycle instruction (load/store, mult/div, branch, jump). If this signal is evaluated
for single-cycle instructions, it can prevent the reg file write enable from being de-asserted in the case of stalls due to the IF stage.

@udinator: Could you please verify that this actually fixes the bug you reported in #216 before we merge it?

