issue_info.body:
from a low-power point-of-view, having the main clock running before fetch_enable_i is set high to kick-start it, is not a great idea ;)

I've traced it up to ibex_controller.sv, where in RESET state, the ctrl_busy is still on default 1'b1. Could we maybe make it 1'b0 in reset state?

To make it work, I also add to activate the internal clock when fetch_enable_i is high, otherwise if fetch_enable_i is only 1 cycle long, you miss it.

